August 4 at 6:48 PM ·

2020-21 RETURN TO LEARN UPDATE: We know a lot of you are curious about what instruction will look like at the Career Center this fall. While we are still working out the details, which ultimately have to be approved by the JCISD Board of Education, we can tell you our focus is having in-person instruction five days a week, regardless of what option students choose at their home school. We understand this will present challenges, which we are working through with our staff and the districts we serve. Stay tuned for an update in the coming days.

Habitat for Humanity of Greater Jackson
August 3 at 3:32 PM ·

Tomorrow is ***BLITZ BUILD DAY***. Tomorrow, 8/4, teams of volunteers and staff from Give Hope and Habitat for Humanity will be on the site of a new build on Wolhavn Lane, off of Clinton Rd. in the Northwest Community Schools school district. The foundation is ready, walls have been built off-site and delivered, trusses delivered... a house is going up tomorrow! If you're in the area and would like to stop by and see some action, we'll be there from 7am - 5pm (ish)... :)

NWEE Art
July 1 at 1:00 PM ·

Good News! Our Art to Remember orders are being delivered today! It's been a long wait and I appreciate your patience as the company had a huge back log of orders to fill once things opened back up!
For those of you that ordered products from Art to Remember, you may pick up your order at NWEE on July 9, from 3-7pm. Please stay in your car and line up along the sidewalk and we will get you your products as quickly as we can.
Orders that are not picked up during this time will be placed in the office and the secretaries will be able to get them for you on Wednesdays from 9am-noon.
Please let me know if you have any questions. I can't wait for you to get your products!

shared_text:
Good Things Going - Jackson
May 25 at 1:15 AM ·

Once again, our community is coming together for causes that are making a difference.

A group of local artists have come together to create a “Quarantine Coloring Book” where 100% of the sales benefit the Jackson Interfaith Shelter! With just a few days left to purchase your digital copy, this fundraiser has already raised over $1300!

For a donation, of at least $5, you can download and print this fun coloring book with pages designed by local artists: Vanessa Paz-Malson, Heidi Rhodes, Zach Snyder, Julie Durocher, Sheryl Amburgey, Kate Schwartz, Melissa Morse, Carey Baumgardner, Rene Wheaton, Sarah Sundberg, and Jodie Chilcote.

Want to support? Download your copy at: https://gumroad.com/l/vdrml?fbclid=IwAR0iPUzYMMf2ijanXoSMyu-spdIyOJ2XGyWaLKRmuA4EbWzPtozzpzalQ6g

Jackson Magazine
May 15 at 4:32 PM ·

Congratulations to Sarah Runkel on being named a Top Teacher for 2020!

Sarah Runkel’s grandmother always told her to get an education. As a woman born in 1919 in the hills of Tennessee, her grandmother saw education as something precious that could never be taken away. It was the open door to a brighter future. Runkel has treasured that advice her entire life, choosing to act on her grandmother’s wishes to not only be educated herself, but to instill a love of learning in the succeeding generations that have crossed her path during her 13 years of teaching. “When it comes to teaching, I feel like I
have finally found my groove; I feel like I have arrived,” said Runkel.

Read the full article in the digital edition of Jackson Magazine: ow.ly/T5zt30qGnPr

JTV.TV
Northwest Teacher Sarah Soper Named MED Regional Teacher of the Year - JTV Jackson

Jackson County Intermediate School District
May 7 at 2:57 PM ·

CONGRATULATIONS to Sarah Soper of Northwest Community Schools - one of ten teachers across the state to be named "Teacher of the Year" by the Michigan Department of Education! Mrs. Soper, who teaches 9th grade English at Northwest High School, was selected from more than 400 nominations from students, staff and community members around the state.

According to an MDE press release, the 2020-21 honorees were chosen for their dedication to the teaching profession, as evidenced by their commitment to their students and track record of service to the teaching profession.

Congrats again to Mrs. Soper - we are so proud to have you represent Jackson County!

Good Things Going - Jackson
March 31 at 1:04 AM ·

For over 30 years, Marino's Pizza & More has served our community by preparing delicious food, supporting countless non-profits and schools as well as employing hundreds of people over the years. Recently, Marino's introduced a pizza kit where families can make a pizza at home, together. This fun, educational and delicious activity is available at every Marino's location in addition to their full menu of subs, salads, wraps and more.

Good things are happening in our community, and supporting local businesses, like Marino's, can help Jackson rally in the days to come.

Please like and follow Good Things Going - Jackson to see more positive stories in the days to come!

post_text: The health center at Northwest Kidder MIddle School will be closed until further notice. See the below information from the Center for Family Health.
shared_text:
Center for Family Health
March 25 at 9:11 PM ·

We have heard your concerns regarding care at our Northwest School site and want to assure you that we take them seriously. For our Northwest Health Center patients, we have decided to continue care with Natasha Klavon through telephone and telehealth visits through MyChart. Also, Denise Provencher will be available at our main site if you would like to schedule with her.

The impact of the coronavirus pandemic has been fast and profound. As Federal and State recommendations for health care systems and health care workers have changed, we have been forced to make rapid decisions on the care of our patients and our staff. Sometimes, we don’t always get it right. We apologize for any stress or concern this has caused for you and want to assure you that we are working to continue to provide the best care possible for you and your family.

post_text:
The Give Hope Habitat for Humanity program is in full fundraising swing to raise the money we need to build a Habitat for Humanity home in the NW Community!

We are selling raffle tickets to win Thirty-One bags. There will be 31 winners!! Every ticket you purchase gives you a chance to win one of the items.
* Selling tickets through the start of our next Give Hope meeting at 6 p.m. on Sunday, March 22.
* Tickets are $10 each AND you get a $10 off coupon for Christi Hammond's Thirty-One Gifts :) What a deal!!

If you are interested in purchasing raffle tickets, see members of the Give Hope program or contact Marnie Hade at NWHS at marnie.hade@nwschools.org

Donations for the build can also be made directly through the Greater Jackson Habitat for Humanity's Give Hope website https://greaterjacksonhabitatforhumanity.salsalabs.org/givehopesign-upform/index.html
